[17:40:49] <[Escape75> So anyways, user and system partitions seem to use the same  structure fat32 with boot/filesystem records at sectors 0,1 and then backup at 6,7 ...
[17:41:36] <[Escape75> But there’s extra stuff in between that normally would just be empty, wondering what it might be .
[17:42:51] <[Escape75> When formatting these partitions from other OS that data gets removed of course
